# Knotwork — the lead: THICK by ensemble, not by one fat oscillator.
# unison 3 = every note claims three whole voice cards, each its own
# circuit (V/oct tolerance, drift, stereo seat), detuned 18 cents
# across the stack: nine slightly-out saws beating against each other.
# That shimmer is what "analog" means and what one card can never do.
# Two saws per card + no sub (keep the top open), Moog ladder at 1800
# with a filter env that BLOOMS up 0.5 oct over 90 ms then an LFO
# breathes the cutoff — a moving surface, sustained (0.8), not plucked.
# Evokes no acoustic instrument: it is a detuned saw choir.
unison 3
unison_detune 18
waveform 2
osc2_wave 2
osc2_pitch 0
osc2_level 0.7
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 6
sub 0
circuit 0
key_track 0.6
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0
pulse_width 0.5
attack 0.02
decay 0.6
sustain 0.8
release 0.5
filter_env 0.5
filter_attack 0.09
filter_decay 0.6
filter_sustain 0.65
filter_release 0.4
cutoff 1800
resonance 0.6
drive 1.5
saturation 1.0
hpf 90
volume 0.5
octave 4
noise 0
fuzz 0
spring 0.1
lfo_rate 0.5
lfo_shape 0.5
lfo_pitch 0
lfo_filter 0.12
lfo_pwm 0
